                    "name": "Fastening Leap",
                    "type": "stat_block_section",
                    "text": "The dig-widget Leaps up 20 feet onto a creature or object and attempts a corkscrew Strike against it. If the Strike damages the target, the dig-widget attaches to the target (typically to the back of a creature). This is similar to <a aonid=\"18\" game-obj=\"MonsterAbilities\">Grabbing</a> the creature, but the dig-widget moves with that creature rather than holding it in place. While attached, the dig-widget can't use its corkscrew. The dig-widget can be <a aonid=\"38\" game-obj=\"Actions\">Shoved</a> off, or it can detach itself with an Interact action.",
                    "subtype": "offensive_action",
